            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> Wednesday, <date><hi
                        rend="underline">Oct.–Jan.</hi>?, 1847</date>./</p>
            <p>God who will bring joy to Zion, etc. May he<lb/> bring joy to the soul of my friend,
                etc., etc.</p>
            <p>Sir:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">At first glance your letter of last week, I did not understand<lb/>
                thing about its contents, since it was written in English, and, up to the
                    pres<add>?</add><lb/> I cannot understand your wishes, for the letters are
                run–together<lb/> require more knowledge than I possess (?), Therefore, I beg your
                pardon a<add>nd</add><lb/> ask you from now on to write in German or in Hebrew. I
                still have in <add>my</add><lb/> possession the sum of $7.50. I have not as yet
                received a penny's wor<add>th</add><lb/> from the prayer books or the pentateuchs.
                For any number that came to<lb/>
                <lb/> I had to tell them that I should send the books on the next day,<lb/> however,
                the prayer books are in my possession, for I received the<add>m</add><lb/> last week
                through Adams and Company. I shall make every eff<add>ort</add><lb/> to sell what I
                can. If you want the above mentioned sum, p<add>?</add><lb/> remind me, and I shall
                send it to you without any delay.<lb/> With regard to the printing of my book, I
                shall print two page<lb/> next week and <persName>Mr. Jackson</persName> here will
                print them. If I succeed<lb/> finding the printing expenses through subscribers, I
                shall come to<lb/> city to make an agreement with <persName>Mr. Johnson</persName>
                and will give him two<lb/> as references, or the printer himself will buy them. With
                all this,<lb/> heart says to you, many thanks for the thought which is
                    equival<add>ent</add><lb/> to an action.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">May the king of heaven increase you and give you length of
                    da<add>ys</add><lb/> to occupy yourself in communal needs in honesty, and
                    <del>mak</del> m<add>?</add><lb/> you continue to9 serve God's name, and may you
                behold the<lb/> coming of the Announcer and the Redeemer and to see the
                    gat<add>?</add><lb/> of the scattered sheep and the rebuilding of the sacred
                mount<lb/> in <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName> and its renewal in the near future,
                AmenƱ</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">From me, the <add>?</add>, who seeks your peace and your
                    goo<add>?</add><lb/> all your days.</p>
